        <h3><a href="/questions/8020/is-unexpected-loss-ever-used-in-basel-ii" class="question-hyperlink">Is Unexpected Loss ever used in Basel II?</a></h3>
        <div class="excerpt">
            In Basel II, EL is useful. It's calculated as

$$EL = PD \cdot EAD \cdot LGD $$

in advance IRB (internal rate-based approach),

Correlation
$$R = 0.12 \frac{1 – e^{-50 \cdot PD}}{1 – e^{-50}} 
+ 0.24 ...
        </div>          
